al happy paths.\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:156:npm run inspector:mock -- --base-url http://127.0.0.1:3000\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:162:npm run inspector:mock -- --base-url https://127.0.0.1:3443 --insecure-tls\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:168:ROOT_PASSWORD='change-this' npm run inspector:mock -- --include-reset\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:171:The local inspector creates temporary endpoint, user, client, and token records, then removes the mutable records before exiting. Audit and token history may remain as non-secret evidence, matching the product's audit behavior.\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:178:npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:202:The repository includes `config/mcp-inspector.local.json` for local targets and `config/mcp-inspector.remote.json` for deployed target checks.\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:208:1. Keep the standalone UI scenario runner and CLI inspector aligned so users can choose either visible browser evidence or terminal evidence.\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:226:npm run inspector:mcp:none\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:234:This repository provides `config/mcp-inspector.local.json` with local Streamable HTTP targets:\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:249:npm run inspector:cli:list\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:255:npm run inspector:cli:call:echo\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:261:npm run inspector:cli:basic:list\\ndocs/INSPECTOR.md:270:npx -y @modelcontextprotocol/inspector@0.21.2 \\\\\\nscripts/mock-inspector.mjs:44:  console.log(`MCP Mock Server local inspector\\nscripts/mock-inspector.mjs:47:  npm run inspector:mock\\nscripts/mock-inspector.mjs:48:  npm run inspector:mock -- --base-url http://127.0.0.1:3100\\nscripts/mock-inspector.mjs:49:  ROOT_PASSWORD=change-this npm run inspector:mock -- --include-reset\\nscripts/mock-inspector.mjs:188:    const posted = await mcp(client, endpoint, { jsonrpc: \\\"2.0\\\", id: \\\"inspector-sse-list\\\", method: \\\"tools/list\\\" });\\nscripts/mock-inspector.mjs:190:    const event = await readSseUntil(reader, (text) => text.includes('\\\"id\\\":\\\"inspector-sse-list\\\"'));\\nscripts/m