:- OAuth login-user passwords are stored only as hashes and are not logged by management APIs\\ndocs/SECURITY.md:25:- OAuth client secrets are generated server-side, stored only as hashes, and returned only at creation or regeneration\\ndocs/SECURITY.md:26:- OAuth browser consent uses exact registered redirect URI matching and a short-lived signed login ticket before authorization code creation\\ndocs/SECURITY.md:27:- OAuth authorization codes are stored as single-use-ready records with expiry, client, redirect URI, user, audience/resource, and selected endpoint bindings\\ndocs/SECURITY.md:28:- `/oauth/token` authorization-code exchange requires the same client, client secret, and redirect URI; consumed, expired, mismatched, or unknown codes fail with OAuth-style errors\\ndocs/SECURITY.md:29:- `/oauth/token` client-credentials exchange requires a valid enabled client and secret, does not require user login, and intersects requested endpoint scopes with the client's allowed endpoint set\\ndocs/SECURITY.md:36:- MCP routes /mcp, /mcp/none, /mcp/basic, /mcp/oauth\\ndocs/SECURITY.md:37:- REST mock routes /rest/tools and /rest/tools/:name/call\\ndocs/SECURITY.md:38:- OAuth browser, token, revocation, discovery, and JWKS routes\\ndocs/SECURITY.md:43:- E2E tests for Basic 401/success and OAuth 401/403/revocation\\ntests/e2e/rest-tools-call.spec.ts:7:test(\\\"REST tools call executes exact matches, Basic auth, errors, and console evidence @rest-tools-call\\\", async ({\\ntests/e2e/rest-tools-call.spec.ts:19:      title: \\\"REST call endpoint\\\",\\ntests/e2e/rest-tools-call.spec.ts:20:      description: \\\"Callable through REST tool calls.\\\",\\ntests/e2e/rest-tools-call.spec.ts:148:  await consoleRegion.getByRole(\\\"button\\\", { name: \\\"Run REST call\\\" }).click();\\ntests/e2e/rest-tools-call.spec.ts:149:  await expect(consoleRegion.getByText(\\\"REST call completed.\\\")).toBeVisible();\\ntests/e2e/rest-tools-call.spec.ts:159:  await consoleRegion.getByRole(\\\"button\\\", { name: \\\"Run REST call\\\" }).click();\\ndocs/DESIGN.md:4:Capture the top-level design direction for MCP Mock Server and point to the deeper design docs that define the real constraints.\\ndocs/DESIGN.md:8:- protocol clarity: separate MCP JSON-RPC, REST, and OAuth surfaces while keeping shared endpoint concepts consistent\\ndocs/DESIGN.md:9:- schema clarity: endpoint pages display MCP `inputSchema` generated from the endpoint domain service, not console-local rules\\ntests/e2e/bootstrap.spec.ts:3:test(\\\"foundation dashboard renders planned MCP mock server surfaces\\\", async ({ page }) => {\\ntests/e2e/bootstrap.spec.ts:6:  await expect(page.getByRole(\\\"heading\\\", { name: \\\"MCP Mock Server\\\" })).toBeVisible();\\ntests/e2e/bootstrap.spec.ts:7:  await expect(page.getByText(\\\"MCP JSON-RPC runtime\\\")).toBeVisible();\\ntests/e2e/bootstrap.spec.ts:8:  await expect(page.getByText(\\\"OAuth consent and token runtime\\\")).toBeVisible();\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:4:Describe the user-facing structure of MCP Mock Server so an agent can implement the UI without guessing the product model.\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:18:| /oauth-users | OAuth users | Built-in default locked |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:19:| /oauth-clients | OAuth clients | Redirect URIs and allowed endpoints |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:21:| /config | Server config | Base URL, MCP/REST/OAuth examples, Nginx guide |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:24:| /oauth/login | OAuth login | Separate from admin UI |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:25:| /oauth/consent | OAuth consent | Endpoint permission checklist |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:27:| /mcp, /mcp/none, /mcp/basic, /mcp/oauth | MCP JSON-RPC | Unified plus strict auth routes |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:28:| /rest/tools, /rest/tools/:name/call | REST mock API | Same tool catalog through REST |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:29:| /.well-known/*, /oauth/jwks, /oauth/token, /oauth/revoke | OAuth metadata/runtime | Discovery, token, revocation |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:36:| Endpoint console | Preview MCP/REST call shape with selected auth mode, run REST no-auth and Basic calls, and show raw execution evidence |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:38:| OAuth users | List/search/create/password-edit/disable/delete OAuth login identities and token TTL presets with built-in default locked |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:39:| OAuth clients | Manage generated client secrets, redirect URIs, client credentials TTL presets, and allowed endpoint set |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:40:| OAuth login/consent | Complete authorization-code flow and select endpoint permissions |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:42:| Config/guide | Show base URL, MCP/REST/OAuth URLs, sample client config, curl, Nginx |\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:54:- endpoint editor forms must show generated MCP `inputSchema` from the shared endpoint domain schema helper\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:55:- endpoint console REST execution is available for no-auth and Basic modes and shows raw request, raw response, principal, matched case, and elapsed time\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:57:- OAuth user forms must not display password hashes, must use bounded token TTL presets, and must disable mutation controls for the built-in row\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:58:- OAuth client forms must not display stored secret hashes, must show generated raw client secrets only at creation or regeneration, and must disable mutation controls for the built-in row\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:67:- copy buttons should exist for MCP URLs, REST URLs, client config, curl examples, client secrets at issuance, and JWTs at issuance\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:68:- OAuth consent should make selected endpoint permissions unambiguous\\ndocs/FRONTEND.md:69:- OAuth consent must show client, redirect URI, resource, login user, authorization-code TTL, and the endpoint checklist outside the public admin navigation\\ntests/e2e/rest-tools-list.spec.ts:7:test(\\\"REST tools list exposes enabled metadata for no-auth and Basic callers @rest-tools-list\\\", async ({ request }) => {\\ntests/e2e/rest-tools-list.spec.ts:17:      title: \\\"REST list enabled\\\",\\ntests/e2e/rest-tools-list.spec